dsDescriptionValue.value:
This unit was presented at the end of each session. It asked Rs to indicate on 0-100 scales: *how do you feel right now, how do you feel about your partner, how do you feel about your team, how do you feel about your department, how do you feel about your division, how do you feel about CAPS.

*Rs were also asked this question at the beginning of each unit. Those data are stored in GREET.

Then Rs could enter open-ended comments or questions concerning the session. These messages ap peared in the daily report to the CAPS manager so that necessary responses to them could be made. Session end time was added to this year's unit.

In CAPS/84 the wrap up unit was administered only twice -- once in each semester. In CAPS/86, CAPS/87 and CAPS/88 it was administered every week.

No standard scoring.
